Ad Text:
About the Opportunity

The Systems Engineer will be responsible for the implementation and application of Systems Engineering Methodologies. They will provide output which satisfies the standards of Austal, with the application of Systems Engineering Approach.

About Austal

Austal is Australia’s global shipbuilder, Defence prime contractor; and maritime technology partner of choice. We design, construct, and support defence and commercial vessels for the world’s leading operators with operations spanning Australia, the USA, Philippines, and Vietnam.

Under the Strategic Shipbuilding Agreement, Austal is leading a new era of continuous naval shipbuilding in Western Australia. We’re driving innovation, supporting sovereign capability, and creating long-term opportunities for Australian industry and workers.

Learn more at austal.com/ssa

This is your opportunity to contribute to projects of national significance. The maritime is now.

What’s Involved

Maintain project requirements.
Manage the engineering change process.
Support the creation and maintenance of Acceptance Test Procedures and Functional Tests.
Apply SE methodologies to produce accurate data and documentation, which meets all procedural and auditable requirements.
All Data & Paperwork is stored appropriately and controlled.
Demonstrates a high attention to detail.
Work produced is of a high quality and consistent with relevant standards.
Apply SE Methodologies within the team to deliver Projects.
Ensure processes consider the entire lifecycle of the product / system in the Austal value chain.
Drive the consistent application of SE methodology with technical stakeholders (CM, ILS, Production, V&V, Projects).
Support creation and delivery of Client deliverables.
Support technical deliverables to achieve system acceptance.
Support continuous improvement activities related to SE tools and processes – e.g. CAD, PLM, ERP.
Ensure the PLM system and 3D CAD Platform operate in an integrated way.
Ensure the effective application of an integrated Library Management approach.
Specialisation Field – Cyber Compliance
Act as primary Point of Contact for Cyberworthiness for the Project.
Maintain the relevant Cyberworthiness and security documentation.
Manage all Cyberworthiness and security certification requirements.
Manage mission system software deliverables for the project.

You’ll Need 

Essential

Tertiary qualifications in Engineering or related discipline.
3+ years experience in Systems Engineering or related specialisation.
Demonstrated maturity and depth of experience in complex projects.
A track record of systems engineering application with proven ability in change management, continuous improvement and delivery implementation.

Desirable

An understanding and practical experience working within a complex project environment.
Practical experience of quality assurance and business improvement process with targeted and effective business solutions and outcomes.
Demonstrated experience in the successful delivery of documentation associated with capability delivery to complex customers.
Practical experience working within a design team.
Practical experience in the related specialisation as applicable.
Practical experience of requirements management and design traceability.
Practical experience with configuration management and associated PLM toolsets.
Chartered Professional Engineer (CPEng) or the ability to achieve CPEng through Engineers Australia.
Member of Systems Engineering Society of Australia (SESA) or the International Council of Systems Engineers (INCOSE).

Why Join Us?

Competitive compensation and benefits package.
Professional development and training opportunities.
A supportive and dynamic work environment.
Opportunities for career advancement within our growing organisation.

At Austal we are committed to providing a safe and inclusive work environment for all. We believe that achieving greater diversity will enhance our operations and as such we actively encourage Aboriginal & Torres Strait Islanders, people of all backgrounds, ages, sexual orientation, and those with Disability to apply.

Learn more at Careers at Austal Australia | Austal: Australia

Experience in cemetery and crematorium operations or government enterprise systems would be highly regarded

If you're a skilled integration professional looking for a new challenge, please submit your application, including your resume and cover letter, addressing the key responsibilities.

Most job ads for data engineers talk about “exciting opportunities” and “fast-paced environments.” Translation: you’ll be cleaning up spaghetti pipelines for the next two years.

This role isn’t that.

You’ll be the one setting the direction. The one deciding how data gets used, stored, and scaled. The one whose work powers AI models, analytics, and commercial decisions, not just another person duct-taping together broken queries.

Here’s what you’ll actually be doing:

Building pipelines in Azure that don’t collapse under their own weight.
Designing data architecture that can scale without burning money.
Creating infrastructure that makes machine learning models work in the real world.
Partnering with product and commercial teams so data isn’t just “available” but useful.
Putting proper governance and observability in place
What you need to bring:

Strong Azure knowledge: Data Factory, Synapse, Event Hubs, Functions, Storage.
Databricks, Elasticsearch, Python or .Net
A handle on data modelling, governance, and security that goes beyond theory.
Communication skills that don’t make commercial people back slowly out of the room.
Extra brownie points if you’ve:

Worked with Snowflake, Airflow, Kafka, MLflow, Feature Stores.
Built AI or propensity models that actually got used.
Seen the inside of a SaaS or startup and lived to tell the tale.
What’s in it for you:

Flexible hours and remote work – no surprises there.
The chance to build a data strategy from scratch, not inherit one from 2012.
A culture where you won’t be punished for learning.
Work that directly influences the success of the product
This isn’t a role for someone who wants to be told what to build. It’s for someone who wants to shape the whole data landscape.

Crushing Screening & Minerals Processing Equipment
Perth, WA

Striker and MAX Plant design and manufacture heavy-duty mobile and modular crushing, screening and minerals processing equipment for mining, quarrying and recycling applications in Australia and overseas.

We are looking for an experienced Controls & Automation Engineer to own the PLC and HMI systems across our equipment range and lead the next stage of machine and technology upgrades.

This is a hands-on OEM role focused on making machines smarter, safer and easier to operate in real site conditions.

About the role

You will be responsible for the control systems that run our mobile and modular plant, from base PLC architecture through to operator touchscreens and commissioning support.

A key focus of this role is upgrading machine functionality so operators can safely adjust things like crusher gap, speeds and operating modes through the HMI at the touch of a button, without overcomplicating the machine or compromising reliability.

This role sits between engineering, production, service and commissioning and plays a critical part in how our machines perform in the field.

Key responsibilities

Own and develop PLC architecture across Striker and MAX Plant equipment

Program and maintain PLC logic for mobile crushing, screening and conveying plant

Design and build HMI interfaces that are practical, intuitive and site-ready

Implement operator-controlled features such as:

Crusher gap and CSS adjustment

Speed control and operating modes

Material or recipe-based settings

Ensure all control changes are protected by robust safety and interlock logic

Upgrade existing machines without introducing unnecessary complexity or downtime

Support commissioning, troubleshooting and continuous improvement

Work closely with mechanical, design and service teams to ensure controls match real-world operation.

What we are looking for

You are a controls engineer who understands heavy equipment, not just screens and code.

Essential experience

5+ years in PLC and automation engineering

Strong experience with Siemens TIA Portal and or Allen-Bradley Studio 5000

HMI development experience (WinCC, FactoryTalk, Pro-face or similar)

Hands-on experience with mobile or heavy industrial equipment

Understanding of:

Hydraulic systems

VSD-driven conveyors

Interlocks and machine protection

Diesel-electric or electric power systems

Commissioning and fault-finding experience in real operating environments

Highly regarded

OEM equipment experience

Crushing, screening, mining, quarry or materials handling background

Recipe-based or parameter-driven machine control

Remote monitoring or diagnostics integration

Job Title: Head of Data & AI: Asset Intelligence
Ad Text:
About nxzen

nxzen (formerly Enzen Australia) is a global technology, consulting and engineering partner. We help energy, utilities, and national infrastructure providers optimise performance, digitise operations, and enhance resilience-combining deep domain expertise with innovative technology.

Our purpose is to advance the national infrastructure that society depends on.

About the ROLE: Head of Asset Intelligence

Location: Sydney, Hybrid

Permanent Full-time Role

This role, will shape, build and enable the delivery of this proposition for all our target market in Australia (utilities, power companies, airports, rail, telco).  It reports to the head of Digital and collaborates closely with our NNNCo colleagues who provide digital twin, communications and IoT solutions, and with our client Partners.  The role is both market facing and works internally to build our capabilities.

Key responsibilities for the role include: 

Strategy & Growth

Define and execute the Asset Intelligence strategy, aligned to nxzen’s business objectives and client needs.

Identify and prioritise opportunities to expand nxzen’s footprint across utilities, energy, and infrastructure sectors.

Work with Client Partners, clients and NNNCo to develop go-to-market solutions and bids that combine analytics, IoT, and asset performance improvement.

Client & Stakeholder Engagement

Act as a senior point of contact for key clients, building trusted relationships with operations, digital, and engineering leaders.

Support Client Partners and Delivery Directors in shaping client transformation journeys.

Represent nxzen externally at industry events, contributing to thought leadership and brand positioning.

Service & Solution Development

Shape the product and service roadmap, ensuring solutions are technically robust, scalable, and commercially competitive.

Maintain awareness of emerging technologies and trends (AI, IoT, 5G, edge computing, OT security) and translate these into practical client solutions.

Programme Delivery Oversight

Oversee successful delivery of Asset Intelligence programmes, ensuring outcomes are met on quality, cost, and schedule.

Implement strong governance, assurance, and performance metrics across projects.

Ensure operational compliance with security, safety, and regulatory requirements.

About YOU

Confident communicator and influencer, capable of building trusted relationships with stakeholders at all levels, both internally and externally.

Proven ability to identify growth opportunities, shape solutions, and convert them into profitable outcomes.

Highly organized and detail-oriented, with the ability to manage complex projects from inception to completion within time and budget constraints.

Possesses delivery experience and sector knowledge, providing credibility to advise clients and shape effective solutions.

Proactive, resourceful, and motivated to take ownership of challenges, delivering high-quality results with minimal supervision.

Experienced in leading and coordinating cross-functional, multi-disciplinary teams to achieve strategic objectives and performance targets.

Focused on achieving outcomes that drive measurable business value for both clients and the organization.

How to APPLY

To apply, please submit a copy of your updated resume. Screening will be conducted as we receive applications, and ONLY shortlisted applicants will be contacted.

For more information or to have a confidential discussion, please contact our People & Culture Manager, Shreya Pahwa on shreya.pahwa@nxzen.com.

The Company

You will be working for an established, privately owned and growing head contractor that is multi-faceted across the Remedial, Multi-Residential and Commercial sectors. We are proudly certified as a Great Place to Work in Australia and are headquartered in Potts Point.

MAX Build finds solutions to complex remedial challenges, delivering major remediation projects, high-rise façade maintenance and refurbishment works, and building adaptations and upgrades.

The Role

MAX Build is seeking an AI Implementation Specialist to design, develop and embed internal AI-enabled systems that support and enhance our tendering and project management processes across remedial construction projects.

The focus of the role is to improve accuracy, consistency and efficiency by streamlining manual processes, enabling teams to spend more time on delivery, problem-solving and client outcomes.

You will work closely with estimating, project management and leadership teams to identify opportunities where AI can add genuine value, and to design practical, fit-for-purpose solutions that integrate seamlessly into how the business operates.

The role will involve:

Identifying opportunities to automate and improve elements of tendering and project management workflows

Designing and implementing internal AI tools to support accuracy, efficiency and consistency

Working closely with project teams to understand current processes and pain points

Supporting change management and user adoption across the business

Continuously refining systems based on feedback and evolving project requirements

Supporting future AI and technology-related projects

The Right Candidate

The successful candidate will be based in our Potts Point office and will bring a commercially minded, highly practical approach.

You will have:

Experience implementing AI, automation or data-driven systems in a real-world business environment (construction, engineering, property or adjacent industries highly regarded)

A strong understanding of how AI can support processes such as tendering, estimating, document review, reporting and project management

The ability to translate operational problems into clear, effective technical solutions

Experience working with internal stakeholders to design systems that are intuitive, reliable and easy to adopt

Strong communication skills, with the ability to explain technical concepts to non-technical teams

A practical, delivery-focused mindset, with an appreciation for data security, quality and compliance in a construction setting

What's in it for you

As part of the MAX Build team, you will be establishing your career in a workplace that celebrates diversity and believes in looking after its employees through individual benefits including competitive salary packages, training, mentoring, career progression opportunities and health and wellbeing initiatives.

Our core values:

Win as a team

Be better

Positive People, Positive Outcomes

Salary: $150-175 / hour inclusive of super or plus GST
Ad Text:
Our client is a central ACT Government agency that provides guidance on policy, economic and financial matters, service delivery, whole of government issues and intergovernmental relations

This role is ideal for someone who has a deep understanding of SQL Server and data warehousing, and who enjoys designing scalable ETL pipelines that power real-time and batch data services for APIs.  The successful candidate will enjoy solving complex data challenges and working in a dynamic and fast paced team.

Role description:

The Data Engineer will be primarily responsible for working with the Chief Data Engineer to deliver data assets in the Revenue Management Data Warehouse.  The work will revolve around projects within the Future Operating Model and will support the delivery of digital solutions across multiple business products.
  
Responsibilities:

Deliver scalable ETL pipelines to support analytics, reporting and API consumption.
Optimise SQL queries.
Monitor and troubleshoot data pipeline performance and reliability issues.
Work with the Chief Data Engineer to implement data governance, security and compliance best practices.
Document data flows, data dictionaries and technical specifications.
Professional / Technical Skills and Knowledge:

Minimum of 5 years experience in data engineering; with an emphasis on MS SQL Server.
"Hans on" experience with data warehousing concepts
Recent experience building and maintaining ETL pipelines using tools like SSIS or similar
Familiarity with API development and integration; especially in the context of serving data to APIs.
Experience working in Agile delivery environments.
Familiarity with DevOps practices and tools (eg. Git, CI/CD pipelines)
Qualifications in Computer Science, Information Systems, Engineering or a related field are mandatory.
Microsoft certifications are highly valued
Consultant: Colin Massey

Keywords: Data Engineer, government, MS SQL Server, API's, DevOps, Git, CI/CD, ETL, data analytics, data pipelines, SSIS, Microsoft, data engineering, data warehouse, DW

About Us

Crossmuller Systems Integration is a multi-disciplined engineering leader specialising in the design, build, and integration of advanced industrial systems across various customers and industries. Our project-based work spans diverse sectors including Food and Beverage, Data Centres, Manufacturing, Recycling, and Warehouse Automation.

The Role

We are seeking an experienced and motivated Systems Engineer to play a key role in the delivery of our projects. You will be responsible for the technical design, implementation, and commissioning of complex integration solutions. Your ability to understand the big picture while managing the technical details will be key to successfully interfacing with both our internal teams and our clients.

This role is ideal for a competent technical professional who excels in a project environment and is looking to grow their career, with a clear path towards technical leadership and mentorship opportunities.


Key Responsibilities:

Design, develop, and deploy integrated control systems, including PLC, SCADA, HMI, and industrial networking.

Architect and implement system solutions that meet client requirements, often involving integration with existing MES, ERP, and database applications.

Manage the technical aspects of projects, including system architecture design, specification writing, and code development.

Participation in commissioning activities, system troubleshooting, and providing client training.

Act as a technical point of contact for clients and collaborate effectively with other engineering departments to ensure seamless project execution.

Provide guidance and share knowledge with graduate engineers, contributing to the team's collective expertise.

 

About You

You are an experienced engineer with a proven track record in systems integration within industrial environments.

You thrive in a project-based role where no two days are the same, and you enjoy the challenge of adapting to different technical requirements and scopes.

You are a confident problem-solver who can work autonomously to lead commissioning activities and interact directly with clients.

You have a strong understanding of how different systems (electrical, mechanical, IT) interact and are skilled at making them work together.

You possess strong communication and collaboration skills, and the ability to guide others is looked upon favourably as a key to future growth within our team.

 

Career Growth

At Crossmuller, we are committed to the professional development of our staff. For the right candidate, this role offers a clear pathway for advancement. We value and will support your growth into technical leadership and mentorship positions, where you can take on greater responsibility for project deliverables and guide the next generation of engineers.

 

Essential Skills and Experience:

3+ years of experience in a similar systems integration, automation, or controls role.

Proven proficiency with industrial control platforms (e.g., Siemens TIA Portal, Rockwell Studio 5000/ControlLogix, Schneider EcoStruxure).

Strong experience with SCADA/HMI systems (e.g., Inductive Automation Ignition, Aveva System Platform, Aveva Citect/Plant SCADA, Siemens WinCC, Rockwell FactoryTalk View).

Solid understanding of industrial networking (switches, routers, VLANs, firewall configurations) and communication protocols (Modbus. BACnet, OPC UA, MQTT).

Experience in database integration (SQL) and higher-level programming languages (e.g., C#, Python) is highly regarded.

Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to produce clear technical documentation.

Eligibility Requirements:

A degree in Software, Mechatronic, Electrical, or a related engineering field.

Available to work full-time and willing to travel to client sites for commissioning as required.

Possess a valid driver's licence.

Australian Citizenship or Permanent Residency.

Lead GenAI Systems Engineer

Permanent, full-time position
Flexible, hybrid working environment
Deliver AI-powered solutions that transform the experience for employees and for millions of members.

At AustralianSuper, we truly care about our colleagues. We know work and life are intertwined. That’s why we support the diverse needs of everyone and have policies that enable us all to thrive and be truly flexible. We ensure diversity is celebrated for the opportunity it provides us all to learn and grow and deliver better outcomes for members.

Your New Role
Are you ready to lead the next wave of AI innovation? As our Lead GenAI Systems Engineer, you’ll be at the heart of designing, deploying, and optimising GenAI platforms and solutions that drive real impact across the Fund. You’ll champion best practices in AI systems engineering, ensure secure and ethical deployment of AI models, and manage the lifecycle of AI infrastructure assets.

You’ll lead a talented team, collaborating with data scientists, engineers, and business stakeholders to embed AI into core business processes. From cloud platforms and container orchestration to prompt engineering and model operations, you’ll have the freedom to innovate, and the support to make a difference.  Plus, you’ll join a team that’s genuinely excited about AI, where everyone has Co-Pilot licences and the freedom to build agents that solve real business problems.  You’ll get to lead discovery, problem framing, feasibility assessment, solution design, prototyping, pilots, productionisation, and post-implementation benefit tracking whilst defining and enforcing coding, prompting, and evaluation standards for LLMs and multimodal models.  You’ll get to guide AI engineers on scalable architectures (RAG, fine-tuning, vector database, orchestration), prompt patterns, and evaluation methodologies.

If you love staying ahead of emerging GenAI trends and integrating best practices, whilst enjoying variety, thriving on challenge, and shaping the future while strengthening the foundations, this is the role for you.  Inthis exciting role, you’ll advocate for GenAI, educate colleagues, and help build a culture of continuous improvement and operational excellence.

What You’ll Need

Proven experience leading teams or projects in GenAI or advanced machine learning systems within enterprise environments.  
Experience in establishing governance and quality assurance process for GenAI solutions including responsible AI controls.
Strong understanding of AI Governance and Risks Management, review, assess, and understand risks associated with emerging AI products and technologies.
Strong background in AI infrastructure management (cloud/on-prem), model operations, and lifecycle management processes, with hands-on expertise in AI cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, Azure e.g. AI Foundry, Copilot Studio, Fabric) and container orchestration (Kubernetes).
Advanced programming skills in Python and familiarity with AI frameworks (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch, Hugging Face Transformers).
Demonstrated experience with MLOps/AIOps, AI model lifecycle management, monitoring, and governance frameworks.
Ability to develop and implement AI continuity, disaster recovery, and compliance frameworks, with a commitment to ethical AI practices.
Excellent communication, leadership, and stakeholder management skills, with a knack for translating complex AI concepts for diverse audiences in a passionate and exciting way.
Relevant certifications (e.g., Microsoft Azure, ITIL) and experience in financial services or global organisations are highly regarded.
And yes—bring your best prompt engineering skills and a sense of fun! We’re a team that loves to experiment, share ideas, and celebrate wins together.

Life at AustralianSuper
AustralianSuper is committed to colleague development, and we support our people with ongoing learning, coaching and training, as well as career opportunities across our expanding global organisation. We offer generous leave entitlements and promote a blended working environment in which all roles can flex, and we’re happy to discuss what this looks like for you. 

We cultivate a workplace that champions safety, respect, inclusiveness and diversity. We are committed to supporting our diverse workforce in a way that is inclusive and embraces diversity in all its forms. If you require any reasonable adjustments to the recruitment process or the role, please let our recruitment team know.

What’s Next
If you’re ready to bring your energy, integrity, generosity of spirit and passion for excellent outcomes to a team that loves a challenge, apply now!

Australian or New Zealand citizenship or Australian permanent residency status is required.

Binance is a leading global blockchain ecosystem behind the world’s largest cryptocurrency exchange by trading volume and registered users. We are trusted by over 280 million people in 100+ countries for our industry-leading security, user fund transparency, trading engine speed, deep liquidity, and an unmatched portfolio of digital-asset products. Binance offerings range from trading and finance to education, research, payments, institutional services, Web3 features, and more. We leverage the power of digital assets and blockchain to build an inclusive financial ecosystem to advance the freedom of money and improve financial access for people around the world.

We are looking for a Data Scientist expert to drive advancements in natural language processing and computer vision. You’ll work across content understanding scenarios such as classification, entity recognition, sentiment analysis, and image/video understanding, and help build large-scale systems that power content moderation, recommendation, and search.

Develop and optimize NLP/CV algorithms to improve the performance and efficiency of content understanding pipelines.
Build scalable models (e.g., BERT, GPT, ViT, CLIP) and bring them into production.
Partner with product and data teams to diagnose business challenges and design data-driven solutions.
Track cutting-edge research and explore novel algorithms for real-world applications in content understanding.
Drive system improvements that enhance moderation, recommendation and search workflow
Master’s Degree or above in Computer Science, AI, EE, Mathematics, or related fields.
Strong programming skills in Python or C++ and familiarity with deep learning frameworks such as PyTorch.
Solid foundation in machine learning/deep learning and hands-on experience with common models in NLP and/or CV.
Experience working with large-scale data processing frameworks (Hadoop/Spark/Flink is a plus).
2+ years of algorithm/model development experience.
Background in content safety, recommendation or search systems is highly valued.

Why Binance

• Shape the future with the world’s leading blockchain ecosystem

• Collaborate with world-class talent in a user-centric global organization with a flat structure

• Tackle unique, fast-paced projects with autonomy in an innovative environment

• Thrive in a results-driven workplace with opportunities for career growth and continuous learning

• Competitive salary and company benefits

• Work-from-home arrangement (the arrangement may vary depending on the work nature of the business team)
